    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-02T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-02T09:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.51/75</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-02T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.04 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6877. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> has gone over with me
                    the telegram he sent July 30 [<hi rend="italic">August 2?</hi>] to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSCA1">Spring Rice</persName> for <persName corresp="#p_MWG1"
                        >McAdoo</persName> about exchange. He represents the position as most
                    perilous. He hopes that the President has seen it and will cause a reply to be
                    sent at earliest possible time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
